data.title: Tasteless
data.text:
We went to Mis Sueno's yesterday, the food was poor at best.   The only highlight is the French onion soup, it was great.  We had both chicken and ground beef, both were flavorless, like they never added any spices

The server was excellent and we had no complaints in that respect.

data.title: Just Average
data.text: A small water and beverage glass is never a good sign for me. That means you will be waiting for drink refills often which was the case.  Food was ok. Salsa was watery. Service should have been better given not many customers at the time. I really miss my favorite Mexican restaurant in West Allis that closed a year ago. Loved their spicey carrots and chips. The chocolate cake was good here. It said homemade but I wonder about that. Overall fairly typical. Place is clean with a good dining room.

data.title: Fantastic
data.text: I live in West Allis and I eat here, either dine in or take out, at least twice a month. I love the variety of margaritas and the queso fundito with chorizo is to die for!

data.title: Very expensive for a Mexican Food Restaurant
data.text: Very expensive food and drink.  Good though... I think we paid 13 bucks or so for each margarita.  Fajitas were something like 18 dollars.

data.title: Great Mexican Food
data.text: Food was outstanding, staff friendly and accommodating, chef is original from Monreals on Bluemound. Margarita's very tasty and powerful. Family friendly, wide variety of salsa's. Pork dishes come mild and spicy, both good. Restaurant very clean. Prices are extremely reasonable.

data.title: Excellent fare at a fair price
data.text: Recently went in for lunch. Got quick, attentive service. Was given a bowl of chips and a mild salsa as an appetizer. Shortly thereafter we ordered form the lunch specials. We both ordered  the enchilada and burrito plate. It comes with a large serving of seasoned rice and refried beans. I had a chicken enchilada and beef burrito and my companion had both in the beef version. All the food was flavorful and not over spiced . Overall a very good dining experience. Parking was accessible through the rear door and was free.

data.title: Did not live up to the hype
data.text:
Not sure if our experience was an isolated incident because we had such high hopes from all the reviews. We went on a Tuesday afternoon, the place was empty. We got  seated on the sidewalk tables, which was nice. Salsa and chips were awesome. Salsa was super flavorful. Ordered guacamole as well, which was good. 

I was hoping to try the Pastor pork but was told they were still marinating the pork so no go. We ordered the Steak Taco Diablo and El Grande Burrito with chicken. 

Steak Taco Diablo was so bland. Meat didn't seem to be seasoned. It was just a basic meal: tortilla, lettuce, tomatoes, meat, cheese. No wow factor. Something that could be made at home for all that it was. 

Boyfriend is a huge fan of authentic Mexican as well as Mexican-American. He really wanted to like this place but did not like his burrito. He also noted his food was very bland. His burrito wasn't even hot. It was just chicken rolled inside a tortilla with cheese on top. Cheese was even rubbery in both our dishes. Rice and beans were also cold. Rice was like the Rice-A-Roni kind. There was the end slice of a tomato on his plate as a garnish. Both our entrees came with a side of guacamole that was a little more on the brown side.

Our waitress was great though. She was very kind, helpful, and there when we needed anything. We were really sad and disappointed we couldn't enjoy our food as much as we wanted to. Maybe it was just an off day for the kitchen considering it was a Tuesday. We will try to give it another chance for dinner instead of lunch.

data.title: Best in Town!
data.text: I love this place! The chatitos and chimichangas are amazing!!! The desserts are also great! I have never has a bad meal here and have eaten here with larger groups and with only 2. The service has always been good as well.

data.title: Great Mexican!
data.text: Love this place! We go here all the time, sometimes for dinner, other times just for margaritas and chips with salsa. The food is great - have never been disappointed.

data.title: Best seafood Enchiladas
data.text: Love going to Mis Suenos. The staff is friendly and the food is amazing!! I love the seafood enchiladas, they are the best I have ever had. The salsa is very good too, not bland like many Mexican restaurants. Pretty much everything is excellent from the margaritas to the appetizers. You won’t be sorry!

data.title: Very good Mexican food.
data.text: We have been visiting this restaurant for about a year, the staff is attentive and the food is always good.  Prices are affordable.

data.title: Steak tacos
data.text: Try the steak tacos and make sure to specify, "with cheese".  They are amazing!  We always get them whenever we go out for dinner here.

data.title: The BEST Mexican WORLDWIDE!!!
data.text: Mis Suenos (staff & chef formerly of El Matador) is by far, our favorite restaurant in the world!!  Consistent & friendly service - always very QUICK.  Warm chips & many salsas right when you sit down.  Tasty Margaritas.  You MUST try the appetizer: Chatitos!  Our families favorite (including some picky kids!).  Thanks Mis Suenos for a perfect meal everytime.

data.title: Excellent Mexican food!
data.text:
For years and years we would go to Monreal's El Matador Mexican Restaurant on 92nd & Bluemound Road.  Their food was always fantastic.  When they went out of business we were bummed out because it was a great place to go. 

Then this past year my friend mentioned to me that an acquaintance of his opened a new Mexican restaurant in West Allis and it was the same menu as El Matador.  I told him it couldn't be the same.  If I ate there, I would know right away if it was the same or not.  OMG!  I couldn't believe it!

Yes, El Matador (Mis Suenos) is revived!!!  I am so happy.

The food is excellent!  The service is excellent!  

If you like spicy or hot food try their Cochinito Picoso hot pork dish available in a hot red sauce or green hot sauce.  You can request to have them both as well.  Also, they have the BEST Flautus anywhere.  They also bring as much chips and salsa as you like.

Overall, the food and service are great so don't miss Mis Suenos Mexican Restaurant.  I can't tell you how happy I am that an old favorite has been revived again!

data.title: Worth Going there just for the Chatitos
data.text: We have gone to Mis Suenos at least 10 times and always love the appetizers and Margaritas.  We always order the chatitos and gucamole.  The chatitos are piping hot and the gucamole is fresh. We have not been able to find chatitos anywhere else in the country. They are unique to Milwaukee. Even in the southwest, we haven't found them on any mexican menus. They are so good I sometimes order them as my entree. The enchiladas and tacos are also our favorite and the sauces are excellent. The wait staff is friendly and helpful. We are always greeted with a smile and have never had to wait for a table. They are always accomodating to our dietary needs and allow us to make changes in our orders. The place is clean, and comfortable with some booth seating. It's easy to carry on a conversation with several people and not feel like you're competing with the background noise in the dining room.  Prices are very reasonable.  We have always enjoyed our dinning experience there.

data.title: Confused by other reviews....
data.text: Read all the good reviews & stopped here while in town. Not very many people in there for a Saturday night. Got a seat right away & then proceeded to being ignored by the staff. Finally some one came by and put salsa & chips on our table without saying a word to us. Grabbed our coats & walked out. Rude staff. Filthy menus. Won't be back

data.title: Great food and service
data.text: The food was amazing! I devoured  the salsa within mins of setting down. It was possibly the best salsa I've ever had in my life. Every single thing we ordered from beginning to end of the meal was Delicious. The sauces and seasoning are very authentic and worth having over and over again!

data.title: Chile Rellano
data.text: If you haven't tried their Chile Rellano, you must. It is the best in the U.S.A. and I've had it in many states and cities!            Vette' Woman

data.title: The best enchilldas
data.text: Most favorite are the cheese and onion ones they do have hotter salsa just ask for it. This is my favorite place for their enchiladas

data.title: The BEST Mexican in the U.S.A.!!  You must try this!!
data.text:
Mis Suenos is by far the BEST Mexican restaurant around.  Friendly staff, and tasty food.

You MUST try the Chatitos for appetizer, and Enchiladas for dinner.
The enchiladas are made with warm corn tortillas & a wonderful white (not gloppy yellow) cheese.

Chips & many different salsas are served free.  Nice atmosphere with a few TV's around, but not loud.  Front bar offers meals there too.

Good for families, date night, business, and even enough room for larger groups.

(Former owners & chef & staff from Monreal's El Matador on Bluemound Road.)
